Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 13:42:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] tools: add validation benchmark notes

Provide notes on how to validate the IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY flag
using userspace benchmarks.

Signed-off-by: Codex AI <codex@example.com>
---
 tools/io_uring/low_latency_notes.txt | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 tools/io_uring/low_latency_notes.txt

diff --git a/tools/io_uring/low_latency_notes.txt b/tools/io_uring/low_latency_notes.txt
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..e0319e3
--- /dev/null
+++ b/tools/io_uring/low_latency_notes.txt
@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@
+Validating IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY
+====================================
+
+To validate the effect of the low-latency mode:
+
+1. Use a benchmark that measures the latency of io_uring_enter(GETEVENTS)
+   after a deterministic delay.
+
+2. Compare the p99 latency with and without the IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY
+   flag.
+
+3. Ensure the test is run on a native Linux kernel with consistent
+   CPU frequency settings (e.g., performance governor).
+
+4. Observe the trace_io_uring_complete events to verify low_latency=1.
